20/10/2003
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan said Saturday (18 October) that all the European leaders he met during his visit to Brussels were highly supportive of Turkey's efforts to join the Union. 
At a press conference upon his return, he said all 28 heads of states and foreign ministers participating in the EU summit in Brussels were willing to undertake economic and security initiatives to help Turkey in its efforts.
In other news, Turkish police detained a person Sunday suspected of recent bomb attacks in the country. 
The suspect is described as a member of the Revolutionary People's Liberation Party-Front and was detained during a joint operation by the national intelligence organisation and the Istanbul counterterrorism department. 
(Hurriyet - 20/10/03; Anadolu Agency, TRT 2, NTV - 19/10/03)
